The paper deals with deep convolutional networks for semantic segmentation, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses techniques for improving the performance of these networks, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) concepts. Additionally, the paper mentions normalization parameters, which are commonly used in neural networks and fall under the category of neural engineering (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses computational cost, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM).
